reply.question: 2. If the app declares the collection of data, what type of data does it collect?

answer.full_answer: The app collects personal information such as email addresses, usernames, passwords, accomplishments, harvests, prize redemption history, prize ideas, prizes created, gifts, friend lists, friend requests, gift history, water history, and interactions with other users.

reply.analysis: The answer was derived from the section describing the Personal Information collected by the app, including various data points associated with user interactions and account activities.
reply.reference: The app collects and processes Personal Information about you when you interact with us and our services, as well as when you subscribe to any of our paid or unpaid services. This may include your email address, any information we collect online from you and maintain in association with your account, such as your username and password, any content or data you record or post within the Rosier app, such as accomplishments, harvests, prize redemption history, prize ideas, prizes you create, and prizes you gift to others, any interaction you have with other users, such as your friend list, friend requests, gift history, and water history. URL: https://sites.google.com/view/rosier-termsofuseprivacypolicy/home

reply.question: 3. Does the app declare the purpose of data collection and use?

answer.full_answer: Yes, the app declares the purpose of data collection and use.

reply.analysis: The privacy policy explicitly states that the app processes Personal Information for specific purposes and outlines how it utilizes this data.
reply.reference: We process this Personal Information as required by Rosier to pursue our legitimate interests. reply.question: 5. Does the app share data with third parties?

answer.full_answer: Yes, the app shares data with third parties.

reply.analysis: The privacy policy states that the app shares Personal Information with third-party service providers, including Google Firebase, to store and analyze user data.
reply.reference: We share your Personal Information with third party service providers that provide services on our behalf; for example, we use Google Firebase (with Firestore and Google Analytics) to store and analyze user data from the app (see here for additional details on Firebase's Privacy and Security policies). Such third parties may further include, but are not limited to, providers of: website hosting; maintenance services; email services; security services; content delivery networks; customer support operations and software services; traffic and usage analytics services; and cloud storage and computing services. URL: https://sites.google.com/view/rosier-termsofuseprivacypolicy/home
